                    </div>
                    <span>This book is a must-have for DBAs or developers who want an inside view of SQL Server's architecture.  It contains very little content duplicated from Books Online and delves much deeper than the majority of SQL Server books available.  <p>Delaney shows everything from how data is actually stored on disc to the internals of the query optimizer.  I find her writing style to be smooth and easy to digest, and I had no problem reading this book cover-to-cover.<p>Highly recommended.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Very good book</div>
